race.comment: Matt Dale trained local GROUP CHAT (8) disappointed when backed off the map at Orange first up and then came back home and produced a big effort, beaten just 1.6L after giving away a big start. She's third up now with more to offer and the blinkers go on again. Ready to win. MIDNIGHT MOOSE (3) was a dominant trial winner and then raced a $2.8 favourite here on debut and was much too good for the Maidens. Maps for the run of the race and with the extra fitness and learning he looks capable of taking the next step. OUR LITTLE STAR (4) has been racing well for the Olive yard without winning. Collett is engaged today and the mare should enjoy a soft run. She has claims as well. JENNI DIVINE (9) was back to her best leading and winning a Wagga Maiden with a bit in hand. Draws an inside barrier and the speedy galloper is likely to control the race.  Fitter again and can't be ruled out.
